    <section class="hero">
      <h2>How We Collect Consent for SMS Messaging</h2>
      <p>
        At SlackToSMS, we are committed to respecting your privacy and ensuring that you have full control over the messages you receive. This page outlines our consent collection process and how you can manage your messaging preferences.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="consent-process">
      <h3>Our Opt-In Process</h3>
      
      <div class="consent-step">
        <h4>Step 1: Account Creation</h4>
        <p>When you create an account with SlackToSMS, you provide your email address and verify your identity. At this stage, no SMS messages are sent to your device.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="consent-step">
        <h4>Step 2: Explicit Consent Collection</h4>
        <p>Before we send any SMS notifications, we collect your explicit consent through our subscription setup process:</p>
        <img src="/images/consent-screenshot.png" alt="Screenshot of consent form" class="consent-image">
        <ul>
          <li>You must provide your phone number</li>
          <li>You must check the box confirming: "I consent to receive SMS notifications from SlackToSMS for my selected Slack channels"</li>
          <li>You must click the "Enable SMS Notifications" button to confirm your choice</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="consent-step">
        <h4>Step 3: Verification</h4>
        <p>We send a verification code to your phone number that you must enter on our website to confirm ownership of the phone number and finalize your consent.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="consent-management">
      <h3>Managing Your Consent</h3>
      <p>You can modify or withdraw your consent at any time through your account dashboard:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Add or remove Slack channels from your notification list</li>
        <li>Change your phone number</li>
        <li>Temporarily pause notifications</li>
        <li>Completely disable SMS notifications</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Additionally, you can reply STOP to any SMS message to immediately opt-out of all future messages.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-information">
      <h3>Legal Information</h3>
      <p>Our SMS messaging service complies with all applicable laws and regulations, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA)</li>
        <li>The CAN-SPAM Act</li>
        <li>Carrier requirements and industry best practices</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We maintain records of all consent provided and actions taken to manage your messaging preferences.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-information">
      <h3>Questions About Our Consent Process?</h3>
      <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our consent collection process or SMS messaging practices, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@slacktosms.com">support@slacktosms.com</a>.</p>
    </section>
